President Muhammadu Buhari and the Deputy Speaker of the House of Representatives, Ahmed Idris Wase, have congratulated former Head of State, General Yakubu Gowon, on the occasion of his 85th birthday. The President in a statement by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Mr. Femi Adesina, described the former Nigerian leader as a living legend and symbol of national unity. He said: “As Nigeria’s youngest leader since Independence, President Buhari affirms that Gen. Gowon’s visionary leadership style, wisdom and disciplined outlook kept the country as one, extolling the former Head of State for faith and steadfastness in God in times of adversity, and courageously pursuing the interest of the majority Nigerians for a unified and stronger country.” The President said he believes the elder statesman laid a solid foundation for the country to thrive, with the creation of federating units, and implementation of futuristic policies like the National Youths Service Corps, that has consistently served the purpose of fostering unity, harmony and expanding the horizons of young Nigerians for life-time opportunities. Meanwhile, Wase in a congratulatorymessagebyhisChief Press Secretary (CPS), Umar Puma, said the contributions by the elder statesman towards peace building, national reconciliation and reconstruction has demonstrated that he was a detribalised leader committed to the wholesome growth and development of the country.